nt on timer can be noticed at the 2<sup>nd</sup> commend done the participant 2 which was I presume the continuation of the previous part.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Adjacency pair:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can notice the adjacency pair in the second part where the conversation between two participants is represented with two different colors and by the definition of the adjacency, the two participants were exchanging their ideas/thoughts one after another. In this conversation, we can see the complement pair in the line &ldquo;and I think if you had the time to finish it would have been very explicit where your final answers were and such&rdquo; which was replied with the acceptance by other participant. We can also notice that in the following pair, one was complementing about the interface by rating it &ldquo;A+&rdquo; where it was replied back with a refusal with the line &ldquo;I didn&rsquo;t make it user friendly&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Acceptance:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the chat, the acceptance can be noticed in the line where one of the participant says &ldquo;agreed, I would also like to see a side by side because I can&rsquo;t remember my answers&rdquo; when it comes to the part of explaining and discussing the complexity of the system/ user friendliness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Repair:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this transcript, the correction is not present and both of the participants were discussing mostly about what happened during the problem solving session and their experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Virtual co-presence:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Both of the participants are virtually co-present during the chat session as well as during the problem solving session although they were solving the same problem individually but after that problem-solving session, both discussed their experience, problems and ideas about the problem solving structure and the system virtually. This activity resembles the STDP (same time different place) however at the end 